President Joe Biden has chosen Rose Vela to be the next Director of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. Vela is a retired Texas State District Judge and Texas Appellate Justice, currently residing in Brownsville, Texas, and Washington, D.C. She has a Bachelor of Arts from Southwest Texas State University and a J.D. from St. Mary's School of Law. Vela has served as a trial judge for two full four-year terms, presiding over numerous complex civil and felony criminal cases. She was also elected as Nueces County Presiding Administrative Judge during her tenure. In 2006, Vela won a contested general election to become an Appellate Justice on the 13th Court of Appeals, where she worked to reduce the court's backlog. Vela has been married for 31 years and has two French Bulldogs named Truman and Teddy.